Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Fields
  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Constructors
  • Deprecated Fields 
    Field and Description
    gobblin.configuration.ConfigurationKeys.DATA_PUBLISHER_TYPE
    Use ConfigurationKeys.TASK_DATA_PUBLISHER_TYPE and ConfigurationKeys.JOB_DATA_PUBLISHER_TYPE.
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    gobblin.configuration.SourceState.createExtract(Extract.TableType, String, String)
    gobblin.configuration.SourceState.createWorkUnit(Extract)
    Properties in SourceState should not added to a WorkUnit. Having each WorkUnit contain a copy of SourceState is a waste of memory. Use WorkUnit.create(Extract).
    gobblin.source.extractor.Extractor.getHighWatermark()
    there is no longer support for reporting the high watermark via this method, please see Watermarks for more information.
    gobblin.configuration.WorkUnitState.getHighWaterMark()
    use WorkUnitState.getActualHighWatermark().
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit.getHighWaterMark()
    use the WorkUnit.getExpectedHighWatermark() method.
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit.getLowWaterMark()
    use the WorkUnit.getLowWatermark() method.
    gobblin.configuration.State.getProperty(String)
    Use State.getProp(String)
    gobblin.configuration.WorkUnitState.getProperty(String)
    Use WorkUnitState.getProp(String)
    gobblin.configuration.State.getProperty(String, String)
    Use State.getProp(String, String)
    gobblin.configuration.WorkUnitState.getProperty(String, String)
    Use WorkUnitState.getProp(String, String)
    gobblin.publisher.DataPublisher.initialize()
    DataPublisher initialization should be done in the constructor.
    gobblin.configuration.ImmutableWorkUnitState.setHighWaterMark(long)
    gobblin.configuration.WorkUnitState.setHighWaterMark(long)
    use WorkUnitState.setActualHighWatermark(Watermark).
    gobblin.source.workunit.ImmutableWorkUnit.setHighWaterMark(long)
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit.setHighWaterMark(long)
    use WorkUnit.setWatermarkInterval(WatermarkInterval).
    gobblin.source.workunit.ImmutableWorkUnit.setLowWaterMark(long)
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit.setLowWaterMark(long)
    use WorkUnit.setWatermarkInterval(WatermarkInterval).
  • Deprecated Constructors 
    Constructor and Description
    gobblin.source.workunit.Extract(SourceState, Extract.TableType, String, String)
    Extract does not use any property in SourceState. Use Extract.Extract(TableType, String, String)
    gobblin.source.workunit.MultiWorkUnit()
    Use MultiWorkUnit.createEmpty() instead.
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit()
    Use WorkUnit.createEmpty()
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit(SourceState, Extract)
    Properties in SourceState should not be added to a WorkUnit. Having each WorkUnit contain a copy of SourceState is a waste of memory. Use WorkUnit.create(Extract).
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit(SourceState, Extract, WatermarkInterval)
    Properties in SourceState should not be added to a WorkUnit. Having each WorkUnit contain a copy of SourceState is a waste of memory. Use WorkUnit.create(Extract, WatermarkInterval).
    gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit(WorkUnit)
    Use WorkUnit.copyOf(WorkUnit)
    gobblin.configuration.WorkUnitState(WorkUnit)
    It is recommended to use WorkUnitState.WorkUnitState(WorkUnit, State) rather than combining properties in the job state into the workunit.
